					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Sorry for yet another dumb question, but I was wondering if it were possible to scale sprites without the need of an expansion chip. I know that the Super FX chip was only a cpu and not a graphics processor, but was able to pull of impressive sprite scaling techniques in games such as in Yoshi's Island. Because of this, It seems possible to use the same sprite scaling algorithm used in the Super FX chip and use it on the SNES, even if it would take a huge chunk of processing time.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

